rComments: Used twitter and just needed to tweet 6 times about the powerpoints, which are posted online beforehand. Don't even need to go to class. Easiest A ever. Great teacher, very humble and helpful.
very easy A. just go to class, do your tweets and do the quick assignments. if you dont pay attention youll get called out, its kinda hilarious. ive taken 3 classes with him and they are all good af

He's literally the best. No final or midterms. You only need to do the 3 assignments (250 words x2 and 750words) and the 6 tweets during the class. Had him twice and would love to have him every semester ! Don't think twice, HE IS THE BEST !

He's a cool prof and I love the whole Twitter thing! He's a savage and will call people out though, so just pay attention, do everything on time and you're good. This class is the very definition of an easy A when it's with this prof, trust.

I've had Pierre Lévy for two classes (CMN 1560 and CMN 2560) and he was absolutely amazing. You have to tweet during the class to explain what the Professor is saying. The final exam for these classes is doing a blog about what you have learned during this class. I would like to have this Professor every semester.
he's the best!
he's honestly the best. easy A. he uses facebook and twitter to teach the class. great prof

Personally, I'm not a fan of Levy as a person. Found him to be a bit arrogant and hard to talk to on a face-to-face basis. However, his courses are VERY easy. If you complete the assignments and Tweet as required, you will get a good grade.

this class is a must take for communication students. I missed the teacher evaluation day, so I had to come here and rate him. He is an absolutely amazing teacher! there is just 3 blogging posts, which are super easy. he took a different approach to teaching, which i think its amazing. if you have the option, definitely choose him

A unique class definitely worth taking, prof Levy actively engages students and uses unorthodox teaching methods to effectively get his points across. Even the assignments were kind of fun. You can tell he is passionate about the field of communications. I found it to be super easy as well. Would definitely recommend.

Prof Lévy is very inspirational as he showed us a new way of teaching. Participation (on Twitter) counts. The final is an informal blog entry about the course material. Interesting course material, hilarious teacher, very easy A (make sure to turn your work in, though).

Amazing Guy. He loves what he is teaching, and it really shoes. The content in the course is interesting and easy to comprehend. Everything is done on twitter and Facebook. The evaluations are awesome, super explained and easy to follow. Without much effort, you could easily get an A. I 10/10 recommend

Very interesting class. You use twitter and facebook. The final exam was a blog  and you had 2 other projects where you basically explained tweets related to what you learned in class. Definitely recommend

If you take this class, this teacher takes to heart the media aspect of it. Encourages the use of Twitter during the class (to take notes). Final exam is a blog entry about what you've learnt. Asks to have a Storify or Twitter Moments to show what you've learnt during his classes. Not too hard of a class but he can talk pretty slow.
very good.  He knows whats up.
He is very nice and funny, but you won't learn anything relevant.  Useful class to get a good grade without doing anything but using twitter and Facebook. Classes never last more than 2 hours

He was extreme unorganized, especially for exams. He would make them the day before and the questions would barely reflect on the class content. His exams take under 20 minutes to complete. He barely had any content for the class so he would spend the first hour talking and telling us we don't know how to use Facebook and twitter.
A prof that enjoys making us read his own texts and barely explains anything at all. Likes to make his students feel stupid and look superior to them. I have learned nothing from him so far
Excellent Prof. I like him applying old-style discipline on today's technology. One of my favourites.
Très bon prof qui est toujours prêt à aider! Aime beaucoup la matière dont il enseigne donc ses cours sont très intéressant! Je recommande ce prof à tous!!
